Subject: src: fix error handling in main thread context
From: Daniel P. Berrangé berrange@redhat.com Thu Feb 26 21:42:14 2026 +0000
Date: Fri Feb 27 17:00:02 2026 +0000:
Git: 2c654f21024cce1858bb35db75b5f5494e69806c

The vnc_connection_set_error method assumes it is running in coroutine
context and so crashes in main thread context, trying to yield from a
coroutine that is not active.

Introduce a separate vnc_connection_co_set_error for use in coroutine
context and make vnc_connection_set_error work in main thread context.

This completes standardization on 'vnc_connection_co_' prefix for all
functions that must be run in coroutine context, as opposed to main
loop context.

Signed-off-by: Daniel P. Berrangé <berrange@redhat.com>

